Key Match Events: Cade Povich pitched shutout ball into the sixth inning.
Ryan O'Hearn hit a two-run homer in the second inning.
Colton Cowser hit his 24th homer of the season in the seventh inning.
Carlos Santana broke up the shutout with a two-run single in the ninth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Orioles manager Brandon Hyde expressed excitement about hosting the wild card game in front of their fans.
Twins manager Rocco Baldelli reflected on the disappointing end to what appeared to be a promising season.
Twins starter Pablo López commented on the team's collapse and how things stopped clicking.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles clinched the top American League wild-card spot.
The Twins were eliminated from postseason contention.
The Twins had a high-water mark of the season on Aug. 17, being 70-53 with a five-game cushion in the wild-card race.
Cade Povich, a rookie left-hander, made his first career start against the Twins, the team that drafted him in 2021.
